      <description>&lt;div id="storytext" class="storytext storylocation linkLocation"&gt;       &lt;div id="resg-s1-44029" class="bucketwrap image x-large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 3000;         --source-height: 2000;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x2000+0+0/resize/1100/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F56%2F5a%2Feae29c154feaad6d04f26efb0ecc%2Fa-installation-view-of-exhibit-moving-objects-learning-from-local-and-global-communities-at-the-asian-art-museum-friday-nov-15-2024-march-10-2025-asian-art-museum-photograph-asian-art-museum-san-francisco-by-kevin-candland-7.jpg" class="img" type="image/webp" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x2000+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F56%2F5a%2Feae29c154feaad6d04f26efb0ecc%2Fa-installation-view-of-exhibit-moving-objects-learning-from-local-and-global-communities-at-the-asian-art-museum-friday-nov-15-2024-march-10-2025-asian-art-museum-photograph-asian-art-museum-san-francisco-by-kevin-candland-7.jpg" data-format="webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x2000+0+0/resize/1100/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F56%2F5a%2Feae29c154feaad6d04f26efb0ecc%2Fa-installation-view-of-exhibit-moving-objects-learning-from-local-and-global-communities-at-the-asian-art-museum-friday-nov-15-2024-march-10-2025-asian-art-museum-photograph-asian-art-museum-san-francisco-by-kevin-candland-7.jpg" class="img" type="image/jpeg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x2000+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F56%2F5a%2Feae29c154feaad6d04f26efb0ecc%2Fa-installation-view-of-exhibit-moving-objects-learning-from-local-and-global-communities-at-the-asian-art-museum-friday-nov-15-2024-march-10-2025-asian-art-museum-photograph-asian-art-museum-san-francisco-by-kevin-candland-7.jpg" data-format="jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x2000+0+0/resize/1100/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F56%2F5a%2Feae29c154feaad6d04f26efb0ecc%2Fa-installation-view-of-exhibit-moving-objects-learning-from-local-and-global-communities-at-the-asian-art-museum-friday-nov-15-2024-march-10-2025-asian-art-museum-photograph-asian-art-museum-san-francisco-by-kevin-candland-7.jpg" class="img" alt="A view of Moving Objects - Learning from Local and Global communities, on show at the Asian Art Museum in San Francisco." data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x2000+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F56%2F5a%2Feae29c154feaad6d04f26efb0ecc%2Fa-installation-view-of-exhibit-moving-objects-learning-from-local-and-global-communities-at-the-asian-art-museum-friday-nov-15-2024-march-10-2025-asian-art-museum-photograph-asian-art-museum-san-francisco-by-kevin-candland-7.jpg" data-format="jpeg" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 A view of &lt;em&gt;Moving Objects: Learning from Local and Global Communities&lt;/em&gt; on show at the Asian Art Museum in San Francisco.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Kevin Candland/Asian Art Museum San Francisco                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Last year, the Thai government sent a letter to the Asian Art Museum in San Francisco requesting the return of four ancient bronze statues depicting Buddhist spiritual figures  — buddhas and bodhisattvas. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;" We did some initial research on these," said Natasha Reichle, the museum's associate curator of Southeast Asian art. "It was not too difficult to determine that they were looted."&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Stolen around 60 years ago in a massive &lt;a href="https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/international-journal-of-cultural-property/article/prakhon-chai-hoard-debunked-unravelling-six-decades-of-myth-misdirection-and-misidentification/F6018E93F8087341014345C099F92790" target="_blank"&gt;art heist&lt;/a&gt;, the statues are soon heading home to Thailand. But before they leave, the museum is explaining how these artifacts wound up in its collection in the first place in the exhibition &lt;a href="https://about.asianart.org/press/moving-objects-learning-from-local-and-global-communities/#:~:text=November%2012%2C%202024%20San%20Francisco,heritage%2C%20ownership%2C%20and%20restitution." target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Moving Objects: Learning from Local and Global Communities&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. This effort is indicative of a growing trend: Museums opening up about dark truths.&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;p&gt;"I would love audiences to think of the return of these objects not as in any way a loss," Reichle said, noting that the exhibition explores complex questions to do with cultural heritage, ownership, and restitution.  "And it's also, I hope, a way to form relationships with countries in Southeast Asia that's based on equity and collaboration."&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Turning a blind eye to questionable provenance&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Reichle said these statues were among the many stolen in the mid-1960s from the ruins of a temple in a remote part of northeast Thailand. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;The looted statues were sold to private collectors and museums around the world by a London art dealer. Four of them were gifted to the Asian Art Museum by a major donor. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-44052" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 1292;         --source-height: 657;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1292x657+1100+619/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F16%2F92%2F4fae58f540799648cbaf90f432ec%2Finstallation-view-of-exhibit-moving-objects-learning-from-local-and-global-communities-at-the-asian-art-museum-friday-nov-15-2024-march-10-2025-asian-art-museum-photograph-asian-art-museum-san-francisco-by-kevin-candland-1-copy.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1292x657+1100+619/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F16%2F92%2F4fae58f540799648cbaf90f432ec%2Finstallation-view-of-exhibit-moving-objects-learning-from-local-and-global-communities-at-the-asian-art-museum-friday-nov-15-2024-march-10-2025-asian-art-museum-photograph-asian-art-museum-san-francisco-by-kevin-candland-1-copy.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1292x657+1100+619/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F16%2F92%2F4fae58f540799648cbaf90f432ec%2Finstallation-view-of-exhibit-moving-objects-learning-from-local-and-global-communities-at-the-asian-art-museum-friday-nov-15-2024-march-10-2025-asian-art-museum-photograph-asian-art-museum-san-francisco-by-kevin-candland-1-copy.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightsp